17/07/2005
ANKARA, Turkey -- Turkey and Spain will join forces to implement a new UN initiative that aims to overcome hostile perceptions, counter extremism and foster understanding between Islamic and Western societies. UN Secretary General Kofi Annan officially announced late Thursday (14 July) the launch of the project, titled "Alliance of Civilisations". He also called for the creation of an international trust fund to support the initiative. (NTV - 15/07/05; UN Web site - 14/07/05)
